    <div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
        <h4 class="header">Regional Status</h4>
        

        <ul class="text">
        
            <li><b>Mojave Desert</b> (322Al). <i>Pinus edulis</i> (or <i>P. monophylla</i> ssp. <i>fallax</i>) occurs in California as small populations in the New York Mountains and Mid Hills in the Mojave Desert. Stands sampled in the northern New York Mountains include <i>Garrya flavescens</i> and <i>Quercus turbinella</i> as associates (Evens 2000, Evens et al. 2014).</li>
        
        </ul>
    </div>


    
	
